# Certainty Before Completion™ (Spec 113)

**Full document:** `docs/SPARK_CERTAINTY_BEFORE_COMPLETION_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Not UI — conversation architecture.** Overrides Save/Export/Print/Share toolbar endings.

Complements: [Spec 110 Completion](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_COMPLETION_FRAMEWORK.md) · [Spec 112 Memory](../docs/SPARK_COMPANION_MEMORY_CONTEXT_FRAMEWORK.md) · [Spec 106 Guardrails](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_GUARDRAILS_FRAMEWORK.md) · [Spec 108 Environment Integration](../docs/SPARK_ENVIRONMENT_INTEGRATION_FRAMEWORK.md)

## Spark Promise

**Nothing important gets lost, and you never have to remember where you put it.**

## Three certainties (before any meaningful ending)

1. **What happened?** — calm reassurance, not "Save successful"
2. **Where is it?** — Business Brain™, project, Business Assets™
3. **Can I find it later?** — reassure, never instruct

If any answer is "no" → provide reassurance before moving on.

## Never leave members wondering

Did it save? · Where did it go? · What was it called? · How do I find it?

## Conversation instead of menus

Ask: *"What would you like to do next?"*

Never end with Save · Export · Print · Share toolbar.

Member says "Print it" → Spark opens print experience. **Conversation Drives Navigation™**

## Quiet organization (background)

Autosave · versions · project linking · Brain · Assets · search indexing

## Retrieval = conversational

"Show me my marketing plan." — meaning, not filenames.

## When cannot save — explain honestly

Never leave uncertainty.

## Philosophy

Spark remembers so member doesn't. Organization = Spark. Thinking = member.

